# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Corporate steering boilerplate — picked up automatically by
#  the Multi-Agent MCP Orchestrator (BehaviorTracker.ingestClinerules).
#  Lines starting with '#' are comments and are ignored.
#  Each non-comment line becomes a permanent behavior rule
#  auto-injected into every future prompt for this project.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# === TypeScript ===
Enable strict TypeScript: no implicit any, no unchecked indexed access.
Never use the `any` type. Prefer `unknown` + narrowing, or generics.
Public functions must declare explicit return types.

# === Styling ===
Use Tailwind utility classes only. Do not write custom CSS modules unless explicitly asked.
Reference design tokens via semantic CSS variables (bg-background, text-foreground, etc.).
Never hardcode hex colors in components.

# === Architecture ===
Keep components under 200 lines; extract hooks and subcomponents.
Business logic belongs in `/lib` or hooks, not in JSX components.
All side effects must be wrapped in `useEffect` with explicit dependencies.

# === Git / Commits ===
Use Conventional Commits: feat:, fix:, chore:, refactor:, docs:, test:.
Subject line max 72 characters, imperative mood.
Reference the Jira/issue ID in the commit body.

# === Testing ===
Every new public function ships with a unit test.
Prefer table-driven tests over duplicated `it()` blocks.

# === Security ===
Never commit secrets. Read tokens from process.env.
Sanitize all external input before forwarding to shell or SQL.